[{"Id": 1010040, "EnglishTitle": null, "GujaratiTitle": null, "RUrduTitle": null, "UrduTitle": null, "Sequence": null, "EnglishDescription": "Sheikh Kafa'ami in Baladul Ameen said: this supplication is for the leader of the time, he teaches it to a man that was arrested but he was later released. If a person find himself surrounded by misfortunes or intrigues he must recite this dua to come through tight situations, deadlock and crises. This dua is attributed to the living Imam Sahebaz Zaman (a). It brings immediate help from our living Imam (a)…", "GujaratiDescription": null, "RUrduDescription": "Shaikh Kafami apni kitaab Baladul Ameen mein farmate hai: is dua ko Hazrat Imam-e-Asr (a) ne us shakhs ko mushkilo’n se rehaayi ke liye taaleem farmaya jo zindaan mein muqeed (qaid) tha aur wo azaad ho gaya. Agar koi shakhs museebat mein giraftaar huwa ho, to usey chahiye keh is dua ko padhe jis se woh is museebat o pareshaani se najaat paaye…", "UrduDescription": "شیخ کفعمی ؒنے بلدالامین میں لکھا ہے کہ یہ دعا حضرت حجت (عج)نے ایک شخص کو تعلیم فرمائی جو قید میں تھا اس نے یہ دعا پڑھی تو قید سے رہا ہو گیا، وہ دعا یہ ہے۔۔۔", "English": null, "Gujarati": null, "RGujarati": null, "RUrdu": null, "Urdu": null, "RArabic": null, "ArabicText1": null, "ArabicGreenSign1": null, "ArabicRedSign1": null, "ArabicBlueSign1": null, "ArabicText2": null, "ArabicGreenSign2": null, "ArabicRedSign2": null, "ArabicBlueSign2": null, "ArabicText3": null, "ArabicGreenSign3": null, "ArabicRedSign3": null, "ArabicBlueSign3": null, "ArabicText4": null, "ArabicGreenSign4": null, "ArabicRedSign4": null, "ArabicBlueSign4": null, "ArabicText5": null, "ArabicGreenSign5": null, "ArabicRedSign5": null, "ArabicBlueSign5": null, "ArabicText6": null, "ArabicGreenSign6": null, "ArabicRedSign6": null, "ArabicBlueSign6": null, "ArabicText7": null, "ArabicGreenSign7": null, "ArabicRedSign7": null, "ArabicBlueSign7": null, "ArabicText8": null, "ArabicGreenSign8": null, "ArabicRedSign8": null, "ArabicBlueSign8": null, 